The Power 2018 season came to an end today in Olean. A sad end to an utterly successful season, nothing to be sad about at all actually. The big return to Niagara Falls and the NYCBL was better than we could have hoped. A rocky start to the year lead to the Power moving from the lower end of the West into third place. Produced a couple of all stars and many great players. They took some big lumps, but put up a ton of runs on some teams. You take the good with the bad in life but here we have mostly good. It might be rough today but everyone in the Power organization should hold their heads high all the way until next season when we get to have all the fun again. Thanks to NU and the whole crew who runs the team for an amazing 2018 summer. See you guys next season! Have a great summer #PowerUp
